author: @17Codiferus
text: 20GB of HDD Space is PLENTY for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS, Remember you can keep user data on separate partitions and mount them in the VM as necessary. I don't know how big the data sets we'll be testing with are but a 100GB Linux VM is almost definitely excessive.
